<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14115">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Indian_Lore.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11903">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Identify the different American Indian cultural areas. Explain what makes
      them each unique. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/q7v3zl5tgKA" target="_blank"
        >Native American Cultural Regions (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11904">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Research an American Indian tribe, group, or nation. Tell your counselor
      about traditional dwellings, way of life, tribal government, religious
      beliefs, family and clan relationships, language, clothing styles, arts
      and crafts, food cultivation, foraging and preparation, means of getting
      around, games, customs in warfare, and where and how they live today.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11905">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11905 mb-requirement-id-11906">
        (a) Learn 10 common terms in an American Indian language and their
        meanings.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11905 mb-requirement-id-11907">
        (b) Identify the meaning of 10 place names of American Indian origin in
        the United States. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.today.com/life/native-american-town-names-rcna176894"
          target="_blank"
          >75 U.S. Place Names Inspired by Native American Culture (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11905 mb-requirement-id-11908">
        (c) Name five well-known American Indian leaders, either from the past
        or people of today. Give their tribes or nations. Describe what they did
        or do now that makes them notable. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/nBYtf58Vpt0" target="_blank"
          >10 Legendary Chiefs: Courageous Heroes of Native America (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11909">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11909 mb-requirement-id-11910">
        (a) Describe how life might have been different for the European
        settlers if there had been no Native Americans to meet them when they
        came to this continent.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11909 mb-requirement-id-11911">
        (b) Describe eight things adopted by others from American Indians.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Stp7uQxj5lM" target="_blank"
          >Contributions of Native Americans—Indigenous Achievements That Shaped
          Today (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11909 mb-requirement-id-11912">
        (c) Learn a game played by a group or tribe. Teach and lead it with a
        Scout group. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Btted7c6Fqc" target="_blank"
          >Cherokee Traditional Games: Stickball (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7ipsFFUyr00" target="_blank"
          >Cherokee Traditional Games: The Game of Graces (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11913">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11913 mb-requirement-id-11914">
        (a) Visit a museum either in-person or virtually to see American Indian
        exhibitions and collections. Discuss with your counselor what you
        observed or learned from two exhibitions and identify 10 artifacts by
        tribe or nation, their shape, size, and use. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.aam-us.org/programs/about-museums/find-a-museum/"
          target="_blank"
          >Museums (Choose option Ethnically/Culturally/Tribally Specific)
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11913 mb-requirement-id-11915">
        (b) Attend a contemporary American Indian gathering. Discuss with your
        counselor proper etiquette for attending as well as what you learned and
        observed during your visit. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://calendar.powwows.com/" target="_blank"
          >Pow Wow Calendar (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/N2CmYbpjIz8?si=B5Ms1k8y5i2ifL_e"
          target="_blank"
          >Celebration of Powwow | The Living History of Native American
          Gatherings (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.indianreservation.info/annual-events-and-celebrations-on-indian-reservations/"
          target="_blank"
          >Annual Events and Celebrations on Indian Reservations (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
